## Model routing (when the main loop is a top-tier model, e.g. Fable)

- Judgment, architecture, taste, review -> main loop.
- Self-contained implementation, bulk mechanical work, log digging,
  huge files, migrations -> cheaper model in a subagent; review the
  result before committing.

Rule: judge the output. Price is a tiebreaker. If a cheap model misses
the bar, redo it with a smarter one without asking. Escalating beats
shipping mediocre.

When a task needs a big, specific pile of context, spin a subagent for
it and hand back a result. Do not drag all of it into the main thread.

Exception: in learning or pair-programming sessions where I write the
code myself, no agent writes it, any model.
